# Zeno Classic Launcher — AI Workflow Rules
# Full rules: see .cursor/rules/android-build-and-adb.mdc and CLAUDE.md

## MANDATORY RULES

### Never Use Worktrees
Never use git worktree or any isolated worktree mode. Always work directly in the repo.

### After Every Code Change — Full Workflow
1. Full release build (ALWAYS assembleRelease, never partial):
   export JAVA_HOME="/Applications/Android Studio.app/Contents/jbr/Contents/Home"
   ./gradlew assembleRelease --no-daemon

2. Install on device:
   adb install -r "app/build/outputs/apk/release/Zeno Classic.apk"
   (Or: ./scripts/build-install.sh does both steps)

3. Ask user to test: "App installed. Please test it — does it work correctly?"
   WAIT for response. Do NOT commit yet.

4. Commit ONLY after user confirms it works:
   git add <specific files>   # never "git add ." or "git add -A"
   git commit -m "description"

5. After commit check: git rev-list --count @{u}..HEAD
   - Less than 5 ahead: stay local
   - 5 or more ahead: remind user to push to remote

### Build Rules
- Always: ./gradlew assembleRelease --no-daemon
- Never for device testing: assembleDebug, compileReleaseKotlin, or partial tasks
- Signing requires key.properties at repo root

### Git Rules
- Never commit before build + install on device
- Never commit before user confirms the build works
- Never use git add . or git add -A
- Never force-push to main
